OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FA generally
OL,6,Fdry evening and night although the odd
OL,7,Fshower possible across the north. Some
OL,8,Fclear periods overnight will lead to
OL,9,Fpatchy frost. Light winds.
OL,10,
OL,11,CSunday:FAfter a cold start the morning
OL,12,Fwill be dry and bright. Thickening
OL,13,Fcloud and outbreaks of rain will
OL,14,Fspread south later in the afternoon,
OL,15,Fclearing through the evening.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Monday to Wednesday:FMainly
OL,18,Fdry, bright and cold on Monday with a
OL,19,Ffew early showers. Sunny spells and
OL,20,Fscattered showers on Tuesday and
OL,21,FWednesday.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
